An inhibitor of Bruton's tyrosine kinase (BTK) with potential anti-inflammatory activity. Upon administration, poseltinib inhibits the activity of BTK and prevents the activation of the B-cell antigen receptor (BCR) signaling pathway. This prevents  the activation of BTK-mediated  inflammatory pathways.
